  "question": [
    "If A and B are two events such that $A \\subset B$ and $P(B) \\ne 0$ then which of the following is correct?"
  ],
  "choices": [
    [
      "$P(A|B) = \\frac{P(B)}{P(A)}$"
    ],
    [
      "$P(A|B) < P(A)$"
    ],
    [
      "$P(A|B) \\ge P(A)$"
    ],
    [
      "$P(A) = P(B)$"
    ]
  ],
  "correctAnswer": 1,
  "explanation": [
    "Since $A \\subset B$, $A \\cap B = A$.",
    "$P(A|B) = P(A \\cap B) / P(B) = P(A) / P(B)$.",
    "Since $P(B) \\le 1$, $1/P(B) \\ge 1$.",
    "Therefore, $P(A)/P(B) \\ge P(A)$.",
    "So $P(A|B) \\ge P(A)$."
  ]
}
